            "description": {
                "S": "<p>The Faculty of Choreography is a unit under the auspices of the Royal University of Fine Arts. The faculty has a clear vision to contribute to the promotion of education, human resource development in the field of arts and culture, training higher education students to become talented in the creation of works of art in all forms of quality, ability and efficiency. In line with the currents of globalization, both regional and international.</p>\n\n<p>All processes and activities related to the curriculum are designed to achieve quality education in accordance with the political programs and plans of the Ministry of Culture and Fine Arts and to be recognized by the Ministry of Education, Youth and Sports. The quality of education in Cambodia and from the Royal Government of Cambodia in terms of better cooperation is in line with national, regional and international standards.</p>\n\n<p>Studying at the Faculty of Choreography, all students will gain knowledge, both old and new, about professors who have experience in both theory and practice methods, focusing primarily on the existence of human resource development. With support from all walks of life with honor and quality.</p>\n\n<p>Upon graduation, students will be able to become full-fledged directors of all forms of drama, dance and circus performers of all kinds, which will enable them to contribute to the preservation, protection and promotion of art, culture, national identity. On the basis of conservation and development in line with the process of globalization.</p>\n"
            },
